    <!-- â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
         SECTION II â€” MAIN CONTENT CONTAINER
         â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â• -->
    <%- body %>

    <!-- â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•
         SECTION III â€” ALPINE.JS STATE CONTROLLER
         â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â• -->
    <script>
        function dashboardState() {
            return {
                timeOfDay: '',
                todayFormatted: '',
                isExecuting: false,
                isRefreshing: false,
                showFixModal: false,
                fixProgress: 0,
                // Initial hydration from EJS payload
                activeLocation: <%- JSON.stringify(activeLocation) %>,
                stats: <%- JSON.stringify(stats) %>,

                async switchOrganization(orgId) {
                    this.isRefreshing = true;
                    document.cookie = `organizationId=${orgId};path=/`;
                    document.cookie = `locationId=;path=/;expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT`; // clear location so it defaults to the new org's first location
                    try {
                        const res = await fetch(`/?format=json`);
                        const data = await res.json();
                        if(data.success) {
                            window.location.reload(); // Hard reload on Org switch is acceptable or we can just reactively update locations too, but EJS loop for locations dropdown needs updating. Since requirement is just "refresh data blocks without reload for specific location ID", we can do it for locId.
                        }
                    } catch(e) {}
                },

                async switchLocation(locId) {
                    if (!locId) return;
                    this.isRefreshing = true;
                    document.cookie = `locationId=${locId};path=/`;
                    try {
                        const res = await fetch(`/?format=json`);
                        const data = await res.json();
                        if (data.success) {
                            this.activeLocation = data.activeLocation;
                            this.stats = data.stats;
                        }
                    } catch (e) {
                        console.error('Failed to switch location context async:', e);
                    } finally {
                        this.isRefreshing = false;
                    }
                },

                async publishReviewReply(review) {
                    console.log('publishReviewReply called for review:', review.id);
                    if (!review || !review.aiSuggestedReply) {
                        console.error('publishReviewReply aborted: no review or no aiSuggestedReply', review);
                        return;
                    }
                    review.isPublishing = true;
                    try {
                        const res = await fetch(`/api/v1/reviews/${review.id}/reply`, {
                            method: 'POST',
                            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
                            body: JSON.stringify({ replyText: review.aiSuggestedReply })
                        });
                        const data = await res.json();
                        console.log('publishReviewReply response:', data);
                        if (data.success) {
                            review.status = 'PUBLISHED';
                            review.replyPublishedAt = new Date().toISOString();
                        }
                    } catch (e) {
                        console.error('Failed to publish review reply', e);
                    } finally {
                        review.isPublishing = false;
                    }
                },

                startAutoPilot() {
                    const locationId = this.activeLocation ? this.activeLocation.id : null;
                    if (!locationId) return;
                    this.isExecuting = true;
                    this.fixProgress = 0;
                    
                    const interval = setInterval(() => {
                        if (this.fixProgress < 90) {
                            this.fixProgress += Math.floor(Math.random() * 15) + 5;
                            if(this.fixProgress > 90) this.fixProgress = 90;
                        }
                    }, 400);

                    fetch('/api/v1/onboarding/auto-pilot/execute', {
                        method: 'POST',
                        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
                        body: JSON.stringify({ locationId })
                    })
                    .then(res => res.json())
                    .then(data => {
                        if (data.success) {
                            this.fixProgress = 100;
                            setTimeout(() => {
                                clearInterval(interval);
                                window.location.reload();
                            }, 800);
                        } else {
                            clearInterval(interval);
                            this.isExecuting = false;
                            alert('Failed to execute AI workflow.');
                        }
                    })
                    .catch(err => {
                        clearInterval(interval);
                        this.isExecuting = false;
                        alert('Network error during AI execution.');
                    });
                },
                init() {
                    var hour = new Date().getHours();
                    if (hour < 12) {
                        this.timeOfDay = 'Morning';
                    } else if (hour < 17) {
                        this.timeOfDay = 'Afternoon';
                    } else {
                        this.timeOfDay = 'Evening';
                    }
                    this.todayFormatted = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-IN', {
                        weekday: 'long',
                        year: 'numeric',
                        month: 'long',
                        day: 'numeric'
                    });
                    document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
                        if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'k') {
                            e.preventDefault();
                            var searchInput = document.getElementById('command-search-input');
                            if (searchInput) {
                                searchInput.focus();
                            }
                        }
                    });
                }
            };
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
